<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-03-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-03-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="110" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d110">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">550 E 1/98</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Italian Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ricci</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <p>The Italian Ambassador presents his compliments to His Excellency the
                            Secretary of State and, by order of his Government, has the honor to
                            inform him that, according to an agreement passed between the Allied
                            Governments, the date of the opening of the International Conference in
                            Genoa has been settled for the tenth of April 1922.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <dateline rendition="#left">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-03-13"><hi rend="italic">March 13, 1922</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>